{
  "texts": [
    "We also measured people's comfort with AI managing HR decisions on firing, hiring, salary compensation, and work scheduling.",
    "Responses were given on a five-point Likert-type scale, from \"not comfortable at all\" to \"very comfortable.\"",
    "The following definition of AI was given preceding these items: \"Artificially Intelligent (AI) agents are smart computers that put into action decisions that they make by themselves.\"",
    "Individual traits.",
    "For measuring the independent variable of the locus of control (LoC), we adapted Rotter's (1966) 13-item LoC scale and reduced it to 6 items (α = 0.76)."
  ]
}